article.description: — Zach Walton scored 17 points and Camryn Winter 16 and Drexel beat Charleston 80-75 on Sunday night to advance to the semifinals of the Colonial Athletic Association tournament.
article.headline: Walton, Winter lead Drexel past Charleston in CAA quarters
article.linkText: Walton, Winter lead Drexel past Charleston in CAA quarters
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- — Zach Walton scored 17 points and Camryn Winter 16 and Drexel beat Charleston 80-75 on Sunday night to advance to the semifinals of the Colonial Athletic Association tournament. The Dragons (10-7) face Northeastern on Monday. Walton finished 5-for-6 shooting from 3-point range. T.J. Bickerstaff scored 14 points and James Butler 12. The Cougars (9-10) fought their way back from a 41-29 halftime deficit and trailed 77-72 on Zep Jasper's layup with 50 seconds left but couldn't get closer. Jasper finished with 27 points and Payton Willis 22. ------ For more AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and https://twitter.com/AP--Top25
